
<p>My poor heart feels like breaking<br />
&#8216;Cause I&#8217;ll never see you again<br />
Still, nobody knows I am crying<br />
&#8216;Cause I&#8217;m walking the streets in the rain</p>
<p>My tears are mixed through the raindrops<br />
And I feel like I can&#8217;t stand the pain<br />
Still, nobody knows I am crying<br />
&#8216;Cause I&#8217;m walking the streets in the rain</p>
<p>I&#8217;m retracing your steps one by one<br />
Oh, we walk down the street for so long<br />
I can still see your face through my teardrops<br />
While the rain whispers softly: &#8220;She&#8217;s gone&#8221;</p>
<p>The tears and the rain will keep falling<br />
Till you bring back the sunshine again<br />
Still, nobody knows I am crying<br />
&#8216;Cause I&#8217;m walking the streets in the rain</p>
